        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/126603513?v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Description</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Added documentation for two new CSS properties: <code class=\"notranslate\">reading-flow</code> and <code class=\"notranslate\">reading-order</code>. These properties are part of the CSS Display Level 4 specification.</p>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Motivation</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Currently, no MDN pages explain these properties. This PR adds new pages to improve documentation.</p>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Additional details</h3>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>These properties are <strong>experimental</strong> and currently only available in Chrome Canary (&gt;= 136) with the <code class=\"notranslate\">CSSReadingFlow</code> flag enabled.</li>\n<li>Sources:\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/css-display-4/#reading-flow\" rel=\"nofollow\">W3C Spec - Reading Flow</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://drafts.csswg.org/css-display-4/#reading-order\" rel=\"nofollow\">W3C Spec - Reading Order</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://chrome.dev/reading-flow-examples/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Chrome Dev Examples</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Related issues and pull requests</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">N/A</p>",
