        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/23019147?u=4c0de81596ced64dc067dea5686f7ca2912db0cb&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/><h3 dir=\"auto\">Description</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #38836.\">Fixes</span> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"2954802233\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mdn/content/issues/38836\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/mdn/content/issues/38836/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/mdn/content/issues/38836\">#38836</a></p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">In addition to the page highlighted in the issue, this PR updates the phrasing on several other pages, replacing instances such as “the below sections”, \"the below image\", and \"the below code\" with clearer and more natural alternatives like “the following section/code” or “the section below”.</p>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Motivation</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">To improve readability and align with more natural English usage</p>",
