        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1612152?u=642b59321f6fe5b2672063be011780e1577d7898&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Description</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">The long sentences and convolute writing makes the effect difficult to understand. The relation between inline-size and the more classic width or height is improved.</p>\n\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Motivation</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Many readers will have met <code class=\"notranslate\">width</code> and <code class=\"notranslate\">height</code> and are quite intimate with these. The suggested change makes the relation between those and `inline-size easier to understand.</p>\n\n",
