        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/105683440?u=fa3168b8b1e165909aa7ad6a09adfcd6ead45def&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Description</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">This pull request updates the code snippets in the <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Reference/Roles/search_role\" rel=\"nofollow\">ARIA: search role</a> and <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/search\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code class=\"notranslate\">&lt;input type=\"search\"&gt;</code></a> pages.</p>\n\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Motivation</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">In the <code class=\"notranslate\">&lt;input type=\"search\"&gt;</code> page, it encourages developers to use <code class=\"notranslate\">&lt;form role='search'&gt;</code> for accessibility. But according to <a href=\"https://adrianroselli.com/2015/08/where-to-put-your-search-role.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Adrian</a> and <a href=\"https://www.scottohara.me/blog/2023/03/24/search-element.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Scott</a>, it recommended to not use this method to make search components in forms to be accessible.</p>\n\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Additional details</h3>\n\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Related issues and pull requests</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #37799.\">Closes</span> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"2810426983\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mdn/content/issues/37799\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/mdn/content/issues/37799/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/mdn/content/issues/37799\">#37799</a></p>\n\n\n\n",
